Nairobi Governor Evans Kidero raised more than Sh200 million on Thursday night for his re-election campaign.About 300 people, including politicians and business people, attended the invite-only event at Nairobi Club. The event was well attended. The Governor s family, friends, politicians and business people were present, a source told the Star.The Star has established that NASA principals Raila Odinga, Kalozo Musyoka, Moses Wetang ula and Musalia Mudavadi did not attend but sent their representatives.It could not, however, establish if Kidero and Deputy Governor Jonathan Mueke made any contributions.No other politician in the National Super Alliance had declared interest in the city county chief post.Kidero has assembled his campaign team and will soon launch his re-election plan.The Jubilee ticket has attracted at least five candidates including Senator Mike Sonko, Dagoretti South MP Dennis Waweru and Nominated MP Johnston Sakaja. Others afre former Starehe MP Margaret Wanjiru and former presidential candidate Peter Kenneth.Read: Tough race for Nairobi governor as Kidero, Sonko flex musclesPoliticians eyeing any seats were barred from participating in harambees as guests from December 7 last year.The IEBC aligned its Electoral Operations Plan (EOP) for the poll to Election Laws Amendments Act, 2016.Section (64) (1d) bars aspirants and their representatives from making "any gift, loan, offer, promise procurement or agreement ... to procure the vote". It states that this amounts to the offence of bribery.But some including Meru Senator Kiraitu Murungi and Igembe South MP Mithika Linturi have defied the law.More on this: Kiraitu risks ban from poll for giving cash at harambeeAlso read: Linturi defies election laws, gives Sh500,000 at church function